# End-to-End Retail Data Analytics Pipeline with Machine Learning

An end-to-end data analytics project that processes raw retail transaction data, performs business analytics using SQL, and builds a machine learning model to forecast sales revenue.

This project demonstrates the **complete lifecycle of a modern analytics pipeline**, including data engineering, analytics, visualization, and predictive modeling.

---

# Project Overview

Retail businesses generate massive volumes of transaction data. However, extracting actionable insights from raw data requires proper data pipelines, analytics queries, and predictive modeling.

This project builds a **complete analytics workflow** that:

• Cleans and transforms raw retail transaction data
• Stores structured data in a relational database
• Generates business insights using SQL analytics
• Predicts future revenue using a machine learning model
• Produces datasets for BI dashboards

The pipeline demonstrates how **data flows from raw dataset → analytics insights → predictive intelligence**.

---

# Analytics Pipeline Architecture

Raw Excel Dataset
↓
Python ETL Pipeline (Data Cleaning & Feature Engineering)
↓
SQLite Database
↓
SQL Analytics Queries
↓
Business Insight Datasets
↓
Machine Learning Sales Prediction
↓
Visualization & BI Dashboard Integration

---

# Dataset

Dataset used: **Online Retail II Dataset**

The dataset contains transactional records from a UK-based online retailer between **2009 and 2011**.

Key attributes include:

• Invoice ID
• Product description
• Quantity purchased
• Unit price
• Customer ID
• Transaction date
• Country

Dataset Source:
UCI Machine Learning Repository – Online Retail Dataset

