---

# ETL Pipeline

File: `etl_cleaning_sql_load.py`

The ETL pipeline processes the raw retail dataset and prepares it for analytics.

Steps performed:

• Load Excel dataset containing two years of transactions
• Merge multiple sheets into a single dataset
• Remove missing values and duplicates
• Perform feature engineering on timestamps
• Generate time-based features such as year, month, week, and quarter
• Store the cleaned dataset in a SQLite database

Output:

`online_retail_clean.db`

---

# SQL Analytics

File: `sql_analysis_export.py`

SQL queries are used to generate business intelligence datasets.

Analytics performed:

• Sales summary across transactions
• Top selling products by quantity and revenue
• Customer spending behavior analysis
• Product return analysis
• Monthly revenue trends

Generated datasets:

```
data/sales_summary.csv
data/top_products.csv
data/customer_activity.csv
data/returns_summary.csv
data/monthly_sales.csv
```

These datasets can be directly used in **Power BI dashboards**.

---

# Machine Learning Sales Prediction

File: `sales_prediction_model.py`

A machine learning model is used to forecast revenue trends based on historical sales data.

Model used:

Linear Regression

Pipeline steps:

• Extract monthly revenue data from SQLite database
• Split dataset into training and testing sets
• Train regression model
• Evaluate model performance
• Generate prediction visualization

Model metrics:

• Mean Squared Error (MSE)
• R² Score

Saved model:

`sales_prediction_model.pkl`

